Heyo Hated, i feel you... Also having an 1080ti but still have a better framerate than you do. I get about 130-200 which doesnt really satisfy me. I play on a 144hz monitor and I'd expect and want to have 300+ fps permanently. Im really annoyed by the fact that my damn 1080ti cant run this game smoothly in all sitations. I must say that i am really picky and I notice it really fast a soon as i get under 144hz. 

Your case sounds even worse tho, makes me wonder if your game is processed by your cpu and not your gpu. Im pretty sure youve already checked that in the Nvidia settings...

You could try reinstalling your windows if you havent done that already and if youre capable of doing it. {{summoner:13}} 

have you checked your task manager while playing the game? what is your GPU workload while ingame? are there any other processes using alot of the CPUs / GPUs workload? eventually u have some kind of mining software installed? 

i dont know how tech savvy you are but you could also try to run the game in a windows VM to make sure that your windows is not the source of the problem... idk trying to help and hoping to find a way to improve my own fps :) 

cheers from switzerland{{sticker:slayer-jinx-wink}}
